title: YouTuber's game console giveaway sparks chaos in New York
description: Police in New York are urging people to avoid Manhattan's Union Square as they try to contain huge crowds after a game console giveaway event became uncontrollable.

title: Top publishing executive dies in boat crash aged 45
description: A US publishing executive has died after a boating accident off Italy's Amalfi Coast.

title: Breaking Bad and Scarface actor dies
description: Breaking Bad actor Mark Margolis has died at the age of 83, his family has announced.

title: Woman's body found in 1996 identified by police investigating Gilgo Beach murders
description: The body of a woman found 27 years ago among the remains of the long-unsolved Gilgo Beach murder victims has finally been identified by police.

title: Greta Thunberg cancels festival appearance over 'greenwashing'
description: Climate activist Greta Thunberg has cancelled an appearance at the Edinburgh International Book Festival after accusing one of the event's sponsors of "greenwashing".

title: Cats to be treated with human COVID medicine after feline virus outbreak leaves thousands dead
description: Cats in Cyprus will be given human COVID-19 medicine after a feline mutation of the virus left thousands of the animals dead on the island.

title: Putin critic Alexei Navalny jailed for a further 19 years over 'extremism'
description: Jailed Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny has been sentenced to a further 19 years behind bars on charges his supporters have branded trumped up to keep him out of politics for even longer.

title: AI look good... really good: Tinder tests new way to pick your best photos
description: Tinder is testing a new tool that lets AI pick your best photos.

title: Andrew Tate wins appeal to be released from house arrest pending trial
description: Andrew Tate has won his appeal in a Romanian court to be released from house arrest pending trial.

title: Zambia FA 'surprised' over misconduct claims against women's team head coach
description: Zambia's football association has said it is "surprised" by misconduct claims made against women's team head coach Bruce Mwape.

title: Russian navy ship appears to be heavily damaged in Ukrainian sea drone attack
description: A Ukrainian sea drone attack has reportedly damaged a Russian navy ship in the Black Sea - with footage appearing to show it partially submerged as it is towed into a port.

title: Two US Navy sailors charged with passing military secrets to China
description: Two US Navy sailors have been charged with passing classified military intelligence to China, including details on wartime exercises, naval operations and critical technical material.

title: Who is Alexei Navalny - the jailed Putin critic some Russians hope could overthrow him?
description: President Vladimir Putin's most vocal critic has been handed a fresh prison term, which could keep him behind bars for another two decades.

title: A presidential campaign led behind bars is a real possibility - this is truly uncharted territory
description: The courthouse where Donald Trump pleaded not guilty to four charges against him, including conspiracy to defraud the United States, bears the name of Elijah Barrett Prettyman.

title: Niger's ousted president says he is a 'hostage' after military coup
description: President Mohamed Bazoum of Niger has claimed he is a "hostage" and that the entire Sahel region could fall to the Russians following the country's military coup.

title: Amateur rapper and her husband plead guilty after trying to launder stolen Bitcoin worth billions
description: An amateur rapper and her husband have pleaded guilty to attempting to launder stolen Bitcoin.

title: 'A very sad day for America': Defiant Trump pleads not guilty - and asks his supporters for cash
description: Donald Trump declared it is "a very sad day for America" after pleading not guilty to trying to overturn the 2020 election result.
